title: pt_file error
body:
Dr. Ravanelli,
I changed pt_file in cfg and now fail. 
Do you have any recommendations or do you need more information?
Thank you and Peace,
Gerard Gilliland

In SincNet_TIMIT.cfg 
WAS:
pt_file=none
NOW:
pt_file=TIMIT_norm/test/dr6/fmgd0/si1564.wav

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "speaker_id.py", line 207, in <module>
    checkpoint_load = torch.load(pt_file)
  File "/home/gerardg/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 387, in load
    return _load(f, map_location, pickle_module, **pickle_load_args)
  File "/home/gerardg/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 564, in _load
    magic_number = pickle_module.load(f, **pickle_load_args)
ValueError: could not convert string to int

In BirdSongs_SONGS.cfg
WAS:
pt_file=none
NOW:
pt_file=SONGS_norm/test/B27000/S27000_XC171727.wav

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "bird_id.py", line 217, in <module>
    checkpoint_load = torch.load(pt_file)
  File "/home/gerardg/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 387, in load
    return _load(f, map_location, pickle_module, **pickle_load_args)
  File "/home/gerardg/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 564, in _load
    magic_number = pickle_module.load(f, **pickle_load_args)
_pickle.UnpicklingError: unpickling stack underflow
